info.title: Klippa DocHorizon
info.description: This is the documentation of the Klippa DocHorizon REST API.

get.summary: Identity Verification SDK Get Session
get.description: Get the details of a Identity Verification session.

parameters.name: session_token
parameters.description: The session token of the requested session.

schema.description: The session token of the requested session.

get.summary: Identity Verification SDK Get Session File
get.description: Get a specific file from a Identity Verification session. The parsed image can be requested by supplying the corresponding session token and file reference. An image is always returned as a binary.

parameters.name: file_ref
parameters.description: The file reference of the requested file.

schema.description: The file reference of the requested file.

parameters.name: session_token
parameters.description: The session token of the requested session.

schema.description: The session token of the requested session.

post.summary: Identity Verification SDK Upload file to session
post.description:
Note: this request is in multipart/form-data.

To upload data to the IdentityVerificationSDK session, the corresponding session token must be provided.

The uploaded image also must have its type supplied. This can be one of the following "PictureIDFront" "PictureIDBack" "Selfie" "Signature" Finally, the file index must be present, to replace a previously uploaded file, upload with the same index.

parameters.name: session_token
parameters.description: The session token of the requested session.

schema.description: The session token of the requested session.

post.description: Create a new Identity Verification session. In order to create a new IdentityVerificationSession the API key must be present in the call. In the request body schema, there are multiple options that can be entered to customize the session. These option are described in detail below.

get.summary: Get a list of jobs from the bank-statement document capturer
get.description: This endpoint returns a list of jobs. It returns when a job was created, what the current status is and the ID of said job. For the filtering on status the following values can be used (both on their own or in parameter array): in_queue, processing, hitl, done, error, closed and rejected.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: This parameter will set the maximum amount of items returned in a request.

schema.description: This parameter will set the maximum amount of items returned in a request.

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: With this parameter you can set the offset at which the items will begin. This can be helpful for paginating the items if there are too many.

schema.description: With this parameter you can set the offset at which the items will begin. This can be helpful for paginating the items if there are too many.

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: With this parameter you can filter based on the current status of a job and get all results with that filter.

schema.description: With this parameter you can filter based on the current status of a job and get all results with that filter.

post.summary: Capture prompt builder configuration document asynchronously
post.description: This endpoint allows the user to submit a document to be captured with the prompt builder configuration model to process them asynchronously. It will return a ID that is linked to a job. This ID is what we will use in other requests to identify your documents with. Examples: use '2-last' for the second page until the last page, use '3-r1' for page 3 until the second-last page. Invalid page numbers will be skipped.
